      • writeRequest

        protected void writeRequest(Connection rConnection,
                            java.io.OutputStream rOutputStream,
                            java.lang.String sRequest)
                     throws java.lang.Exception
        Must be implemented by subclasses to write a request to the given output stream of the current socket if not overriding SocketEndpoint.SocketRequest.sendRequest(Connection, OutputStream, InputStream, Object). The implementation doesn't need to flush the output stream, this will be handled by the base implementation. But it may be necessary to flush stream wrappers like instances of Writer.

        The default implementation does nothing.

        Overrides:
        writeRequest in class SocketEndpoint.SocketRequest<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
        Parameters:
        rConnection - The connection to write the request to
        rOutputStream - The socket output stream to write to
        sRequest - The request to write
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Any exception may be thrown to indicate errors
